dinary life as a child and young man, but after two serious illnesses, a period of military service, and a year as a prisoner of war in Perugia, he turned from the world and devoted himself to caring for the poor and sick. He was joined by groups of disciples, calling themselves ‘minor friars’ (<i>friari minores</i>). The main features of the Franciscan rule are humility, poverty, and love for all living creatures. The given name occurs occasionally in England as early as  1300 , and more frequently from the early 16th century, when there was a surge of admiration for, and imitation of, Italian Renaissance culture."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Francis Myles was born about 1435. He had at least 1 son with Alice."},"et":{"abt 1435–":"umbes 1435–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1463–1541":"1463–1541","1435–Male":"1435–Surnud","abt 1435":"umbes 1435","1435":"1435","1541":"1541","1463":"1463","Sedgley, Staffordshire, England":"Sedgley, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"abt 1435–":"noin 1435–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1463–1541":"1463–1541","1435–Male":"1435–Kuollut","abt 1435":"noin 1435","1435":"1435","1541":"1541","1463":"1463","Sedgley, Staffordshire, England":"Sedgley, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"abt 1435–":"environ 1435–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1463–1541":"1463–1541","1435–Male":"1435–Décédé","abt 1435":"environ 1435","1435":"1435","1541":"1541","1463":"1463","Sedgley, Staffordshire, England":"Sedgley, Staffordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Francis Myles est né environ 1435. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Alice."},"de":{"abt 1435–":"um 1435–Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1463–1541":"1463–1541","1435–Male":"1435–Verstorben","abt 1435":"um 1435","1435":"1435","1541":"1541","1463":"1463","Sedgley, Staffordshire, England":"Sedgley, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Francis Myles wurde um 1435 geboren. Er hatte mit Alice mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"abt 1435–":"about 1435–Desede",